snippet.textDisplay: All the best Philander. A very underrated player as he was often in the shadow of Steyn and Morkel, and probably Kallis to some extent. He started his career quite late but for a bowling all rounder please take a bow peeps. Over 200 wickets at around 22 a piece and around low 30s with the bat. Bear in mind he was all ways 1st or even 2nd bowling change so he could of had lots more then the 200 odd he finished his career with. It's worth noting He is the last component of Graems Smiths Gladiators 2003 - 2014 which had two great teams with philander playing in the more recent team that ranked number 1 after beating the aussies down under in 2008-09. Side note: Smiths 1st team was absolute class and the only thing separating them from the Great Aussie side of 99-2007 was their lack of skilled spin selection available and also the polar opposite in the case of the aussies having a once in a century spin bowler in Shane warne. Of course the incredible Jaque Kallis gave them an dimension in terms of being selected for both bat or ball and if you took one discipline away he would still be selected such was the brilliance of him being the best all rounder ever! All things considered then they were evenly matched.
